## Handoff Notes

- Use the handoff channel for cross-agent transfers.
- When assigning work to another agent in the handoff channel, start the message with that agent's literal tag/mention so the runtime routes it.
- If you cannot tag the receiving agent, do not assume the handoff succeeded; ask the owner to route it manually or use the receiving agent's direct channel.
- Keep handoffs compact and evidence-backed.
- Never include secrets in handoffs.
